{"parentUuid":"ab7c0a99-e76b-4748-ba39-5e50b6d5b3d4","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01ARBvHprQTEpAY42WzphJhy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the root cause and fixed it.\n\n## What was happening\n\nThe \"unknown channel NAK\" error was an actual bug, not a test-server artifact. I traced it by intercepting the raw upload-pack response bytes for the replicate-rewind scenario:\n\n```\npkt len=0008 channel=4e content=\"NAK\\n\"   ← consumed by ServerResponse.Decode\npkt len=0008 channel=4e content=\"NAK\\n\"   ← leftover — becomes the demuxer's input\npkt len=0009 channel=01 content=\"\\x01PACK\"\npkt len=0009 channel=01 content=\"\\x01\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x02\"\n…\n```\n\ngo-git v6's `plumbing/transport/upload_pack.go` writes **two** NAK pktlines when the client sends haves but none are reachable from the wants. The first comes from the `if len(haves) > 0` branch (writes ACKs — empty list → NAK), the second from the \"no common ack found\" branch right below it. Client-side `packp.ServerResponse.Decode` stops after the first NAK, so the sideband demuxer sees the second one's payload (`NAK\\n`) and reads `'N'` (0x4E) as the channel byte — fails with \"unknown channel NAK\".\n\n## Why existing tests didn't catch it\n\nBoth `fetchToStoreV1` (materialized path, `sync --force`) and `fetchPackV1` (relay path, replicate) hit this. The `TestRun_IntegrationTagsPruneAndForce` test appeared to pass only because its divergent scenario also had *other* refs whose hashes were reachable from the wants, producing an ACK and avoiding the double-NAK branch. My replicate rewind test with a single have was the minimal trigger.\n\n## Fix\n\nWrapped the post-`Decode` reader in `bufio.Reader` and drain any additional `0008NAK\\n` pktlines before handing to the sideband demuxer. Applied to both `fetchToStoreV1` and `fetchPackV1`.\n\n## Commit\n\n`b5fdb49 Drain go-git upload-pack double-NAK before sideband demux`\n- `internal/gitproto/fetch.go` — `drainTrailingNAKs` helper + call sites\n- `internal/gitproto/fetch_test.go` — `TestFetchPackV1DrainsSecondNAK` direct unit test\n- `internal/syncer/integration_test.go` — reverted the V2 workaround in `TestRun_IntegrationReplicateOverwritesDivergentBranch`; passes on V1 now\n\nFull suite green. Worth considering whether to report this upstream to go-git — their own client can't parse their own server's output for this case."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":230,"cache_read_input_tokens":225348,"output_tokens":898,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":230,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011Ca1yJ3cXcCZn8SzuahEZy","type":"assistant","uuid":"0f88f99e-a616-4e45-8c94-ad7d786f1dcd","timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:01:34.856Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"7b2777b1-8075-41f4-a62a-cbfc1b76c01b","version":"2.1.91","gitBranch":"soph/replicate","slug":"clever-popping-whisper"}
