{"parentUuid":"47d0303e-4392-4b6a-b5e8-a06c4cae62cf","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FnBbsciDJu8YbLcEiC7XPX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## State of replicate (branch `soph/replicate`)\n\n**5 commits ahead of main:**\n\n```\nb5fdb49 Drain go-git upload-pack double-NAK before sideband demux\na9b1834 Add CLI tests for replicate subcommand and --force rejection\n307d008 Add integration tests for replicate happy paths and --force rejection\n3486c1b Expose replicate mode in API and CLI\nf377186 Add relay-only replicate engine mode\n```\n\n## Feature\n\n- New `git-sync replicate` subcommand + `plan --mode replicate`\n- New `gitsync.ModeReplicate` on the stable API (`Client.Replicate`) and unstable API\n- Source-authoritative overwrite semantics: divergent branches/tags retargeted, orphan managed refs deleted under `--prune`\n- Relay-only execution; no materialized fallback — incompatible targets (`no-thin`) fail with \"use sync instead\"\n- Rejects `--force` at session construction — force is a sync concept\n\n## Test coverage\n\n| Layer | Tests |\n|---|---|\n| Planner | `PlanReplicationRef` overwrite (branch + tag), `CanReplicateRelay` rejects no-thin + invalid actions |\n| Strategy | `Execute` relays updates + deletes separately (fake pusher) |\n| Syncer integration | Rejects no-thin target, rejects prune-into-bootstrap, **overwrites divergent branch**, **bootstraps empty target**, **retargets divergent tag**, **prunes orphan ref alongside update**, **rejects --force at session construction** |\n| Bridge | `FromSyncResult` carries `operation_mode` + renamed `transfer_mode` |\n| Public client | `Validate()` rejects bogus modes |\n| CLI | `plan --mode replicate` JSON, `replicate` subcommand JSON end-to-end, `replicate --force` rejection |\n\nFull suite green on V1 and V2 protocols.\n\n## Known issue (worked around)\n\nDiscovered during test authoring: go-git's `transport.UploadPack` emits a double NAK when haves aren't reachable from wants, which breaks the standard client pipeline. Fixed upstream (PR branch in `../../go-git`: `fix/upload-pack-double-nak`) and worked around locally in `internal/gitproto/fetch.go` via `drainTrailingNAKs`. The workaround can be removed once the go-git bump includes the fix.\n\n## Open items before merging\n\n- **Breaking JSON rename** in the stable surface: `execution.mode` → `execution.transfer_mode`, plus new top-level `operation_mode` on `syncer.Result`. Worth a CHANGELOG note if any external consumers parse that field.\n- **Small cleanups** from the earlier review still outstanding: `defaultOperationMode` has a dead branch, `BuildReplicationPlans` mutates its caller's `managed` map. Neither is correctness-critical.\n- **V1 empty-pack path** still relies on the drainer workaround until the go-git PR lands. No action needed unless you want to vendor the fix.\n\nReady to ship otherwise."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1071,"cache_read_input_tokens":253440,"output_tokens":1061,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1071,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011Ca1zaMjkj3Vs79WaohdG1","type":"assistant","uuid":"e67fe474-fd27-4ae9-833a-e5908d74aefe","timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:18:31.949Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"7b2777b1-8075-41f4-a62a-cbfc1b76c01b","version":"2.1.91","gitBranch":"soph/replicate","slug":"clever-popping-whisper"}
